âœ¨ Q26: Remove Duplicates from Sorted Array âœ¨
ğŸ“Œ (Hinglish + Short + Coding Style)
ğŸ§® Given: Ek integer array nums diya hai, jo sorted (non-decreasing order) me hai.
ğŸ› ï¸ Task:
Same number baar-baar repeat ho raha ho to duplicates ko remove karo (in-place) ğŸ‘‡
â¡ï¸ Har unique element sirf ek baar array me rehna chahiye.
â¡ï¸ Relative order same rehna chahiye (sorting disturb nahi honi chahiye).

ğŸ¯ Output:
Array me unique elements ki count k return karo.
ğŸ“ nums ke first k elements me sorted unique values honi chahiye.
ğŸ“ k ke baad wale elements ignore kar sakte ho.

ğŸ’¡ Simple Samajh:
Sorted array me se duplicate hatao, aur kitne unique elements bach gaye woh k batao. ğŸ˜„
ğŸ”¥ Example:
[1,1,2,2,2,3] â†’ unique = [1,2,3] â†’ k = 3


import java.util.*;
public class Coding {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int arr[] = {1,2,3,3,4,4,4};   // ğŸ“Œ Sorted array with duplicates
        int k = 1;                     // ğŸ Pointer to track unique elements
        for(int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {   // ğŸ” Loop from second element onwards           
            if(arr[i] != arr[k - 1]) {         // âœ¨ Check: current != last unique
                arr[k] = arr[i];               // ğŸ—ï¸ Store unique element at index k
                k++;                           // â« Increase unique count
            }
        }
        // ğŸ–¨ï¸ Print only the unique elements (first k elements)
        for(int i = 0; i < k; i++) {
            System.out.print(arr[i] + " ");    // ğŸ“¤ Output: 1 2 3 4
        }
    }
}

